The Best Electricians in Canberra

Stuart McMaster from Complete Electrical Service, one of Canberra’s most trusted electricians. Photo: Region Media.

When it comes to electrical work around your home, there is no question that a fully trained and experienced tradie is the only person who should be trusted to complete the job. Apart from the fact it is illegal in Australia to carry out electrical work if you are not a qualified electrician, it is also extremely dangerous. So it is vital for the safety of you and your family that you call in an expert who you can trust.

In Canberra and throughout the local region, there are many experienced electricians who can satisfy all your electrical needs with quality assurance you can depend on. Whether your home requires installation of lighting or appliances, rewiring, an electrical safety check, a complete smart wiring overhaul, or you simply have a niggling issue that needs resolving, there are plenty of dependable, efficient options around town for you to choose from.

We asked our readers from Canberra and the surrounding region to share their experiences with leading local electricians. Below, you will find a recommended list of the best ones. If you are not sure what you are looking for, the following checklist should help you decide which trustworthy sparkie is for you.

What makes a great electrician?

  • Relevant qualifications and licenses. In the ACT, all electrical contractors must be licensed. This gives you peace of mind knowing your electrician has the experience and qualifications to safely conduct all electrical work, from straightforward jobs to complex wiring.
  • Knowledgeable. It pays to do some research and hire an electrician with a wealth of knowledge that only experience can deliver. The best electricians know the ins and outs of the trade. From simple household jobs to electrical emergencies, you need to be assured they can complete the job professionally.
  • Reliable. The best electricians turn up on time, every time, and don’t leave you waiting. They should arrive when they say they will, be ready to work and complete the job efficiently.
  • Transparent pricing. Your electrician should be upfront with you about how much things will cost. Quotes and invoices should be transparent, with no unexpected fees or charges. If any unforeseen expenses arise, you should be confident knowing this will be communicated to you and that you are getting what you pay for.
  • Reliable and respectful of your property. The best electricians treat your home as if it is their own. This means keeping mess and disruption to a minimum while being careful with your belongings.

The best electricians in Canberra

RiotACT’s editorial team has combed through 19 years of onsite comments to compile a list of the most recommended businesses according to you.

To be listed in our Best of Canberra series, each business needs to have consistently received positive feedback on RiotACT and Facebook, as well as maintaining a minimum average of 4/5 stars on Google.

Complete Electrical Service

Complete Electrical Service is one of Canberra’s leading electrical providers. The team prides itself on using premium quality products and materials, always prioritising customer service, and handling every project from start to finish.

Complete Electrical Service electricians are selected for their personality and electrical skills. They receive ongoing training in the latest techniques to ensure their work is safe, efficient and delivered to a superior standard.

They offer an on-time guarantee and free testing of safety switches with every job. Additionally, if you book online you save 10 per cent on the service call fee.

Here is what happy customer Paul had to say about his experience with Complete Electrical Service: “Excellent service. They were able to provide someone at short notice for a quote, and again at short notice for repairs. The electricians were friendly, easy to talk to, did great work and, unprompted, offered suggestions to reduce my power bills, which I will be taking up. They are now in my phone as the go-to electricians.”

Phone: 02 6188 7021 stuart@completeelectricalservice.com.au completeelectricalservice.com.au
Unit 4, 16 Grimwade Street
Mitchell ACT 2911

Harrison's Electrical Canberra

With two fully-qualified, licensed electricians – Harrison McIntyre and Rowan Harrison – at the helm, Harrison’s Electrical Canberra can install, repair and maintain the electrics in your home or commercial space. Their range of services include general electrical work; installation of air-conditioning units; TV, data and telephone outputs; switchboard upgrades; smoke alarm installation and testing; thermal scanning; and commercial fit-outs.

Harrison’s Electrical Canberra guarantees superior customer service, and will always turn up on time to provide outstanding workmanship. Your safety is the duo’s number-one concern, and they will do everything possible to keep the power in your home or commercial premises in safe working order.

Phone: 02 6189 2711 admin@harrisonselec.com.au harrisonselec.com.au

JM Electrical Solutions

Family-owned and locally operated, JM Electrical Solutions offers 24/7 electrical services throughout the Canberra region. With customer service their priority, they guarantee premium electrical work and value for money. Offering a full range of domestic electrical installations – including switchboard upgrades, wiring safety inspections, security lighting, ceiling fans, smoke detectors and TV antennas – you are guaranteed the job will be done right. They also specialise in the supply and fitting of air-conditioning units. With no hidden fees and years of experience, JM Electrical Solutions is a professional company you can trust.

Mark Rawstorn Electrical

Mark Rawstorn is an experienced Canberra electrician providing electrical installation, maintenance and repair to residential and commercial spaces. Quality, safety and professional service are Mark’s priorities, and he has been recognised for delivering excellence in the capital region by business review company Three Best Rated. Catering for all domestic electrical jobs such as lighting, wiring and switchboard upgrades, he operates Monday to Friday plus Saturday by appointment, and on Sunday for emergency call-outs.

Sparks Fly Electrical

Sparks Fly Electrical is a leading Canberra electrical services company that prides itself on delivering quality, professional service and workmanship. With years of experience in the construction industry, the dedicated team of qualified tradies are committed to satisfying the electrical needs of every customer. Their expertise extends across residential and commercial premises, and no job is too big or too small, from power point installations to complete commercial fit-outs. Plastering services are also available and can be quoted as part of your job if you require holes repaired from the repositioning of switches, lights, fans and other appliances.

Frequently Asked Questions

Am I allowed to do small DIY electrical jobs at home?
Absolutely not. Apart from the fact it is illegal to undertake electrical work at home unless you are a qualified electrician, it is also extremely dangerous if you don't fully understand what you are doing. If you are a licensed tradie, then go for it, but everyone else must call upon the services of a fully trained and experienced electrical tradesperson.
What are the ramifications of illegal DIY electrical work?
In the worst case scenario: death. Electrical wiring work can be extremely dangerous so if you are unqualified and something goes wrong, the consequences can be fatal. There is also the possibility of causing a house fire. Fines also apply for performing illegal electrical wiring work around the home. For individuals, this can be as high as $40,000.
What DIY electrical work is legal for me to perform at home?
Some very basic electrical jobs can be carried out at home if you are unqualified. These include installing low voltage garden lighting and pond pumps; changing a blown light bulb; installing battery operated smoke alarms; replacing LED downlights; cutting openings for air-conditioning units but not installing them; and fitting an electric wall oven but not connecting it. For everything else, use one of Canberra's best trained electricians.
When should I arrange an electrical safety check?
At a minimum, you should call a qualified electrician to visit your home for an electrical safety check to ensure everything is in safe working order every five years. If your property is more than 25 years old, a safety check is highly recommended, or if you simply have any concerns about how electrical items in your home have been installed. If you are purchasing a property that has been occupied, an electrical safety check is essential so you know you are buying somewhere safe.
What is smart wiring and who can install it?
Smart wiring is a flexible industry wiring standard that enables the combination of several types of wires into a single platform for use with smart home systems and sensors. Once installed, it allows you to access multiple telephone, internet and pay TV options, as well as audio, security, automated home lighting and integrated garden irrigation. Smart wiring systems can only be installed by an accredited smart wiring technician.

[https://the-riotact.com/could-you-buy-or-sell-a-house-online-heres-how-one-canberra-firm-is-making-it-work/367793] Best of Canberra[https://the-riotact.com/category/community/best-of-canberra] The Best Electricians in Canberra ================================= Stuart McMaster from Complete Electrical Service, one of Canberra’s most trusted electricians. Photo: Region Media. When it comes to electrical work around your home, there is no question that a fully trained and experienced tradie is the only person who should be trusted to complete the job. Apart from the fact it is illegal in Australia to carry out electrical work if you are not a qualified electrician, it is also extremely dangerous. So it is vital for the safety of you and your family that you call in an expert who you can trust. In Canberra and throughout the local region, there are many experienced electricians who can satisfy all your electrical needs with quality assurance you can depend on. Whether your home requires installation of lighting or appliances, rewiring, an electrical safety check, a complete smart wiring overhaul, or you simply have a niggling issue that needs resolving, there are plenty of dependable, efficient options around town for you to choose from. We asked our readers from Canberra and the surrounding region to share their experiences with leading local electricians. Below, you will find a recommended list of the best ones. If you are not sure what you are looking for, the following checklist should help you decide which trustworthy sparkie is for you. What makes a great electrician? ------------------------------- * Relevant qualifications and licenses. In the ACT, all electrical contractors must be licensed. This gives you peace of mind knowing your electrician has the experience and qualifications to safely conduct all electrical work, from straightforward jobs to complex wiring. * Knowledgeable. It pays to do some research and hire an electrician with a wealth of knowledge that only experience can deliver. The best electricians know the ins and outs of the trade. From simple household jobs to electrical emergencies, you need to be assured they can complete the job professionally. * Reliable. The best electricians turn up on time, every time, and don’t leave you waiting. They should arrive when they say they will, be ready to work and complete the job efficiently. * Transparent pricing. Your electrician should be upfront with you about how much things will cost. Quotes and invoices should be transparent, with no unexpected fees or charges. If any unforeseen expenses arise, you should be confident knowing this will be communicated to you and that you are getting what you pay for. * Reliable and respectful of your property. The best electricians treat your home as if it is their own. This means keeping mess and disruption to a minimum while being careful with your belongings. The best electricians in Canberra --------------------------------- RiotACT’s editorial team has combed through 19 years of onsite comments to compile a list of the most recommended businesses according to you. To be listed in our Best of Canberra series, each business needs to have consistently received positive feedback on RiotACT and Facebook, as well as maintaining a minimum average of 4/5 stars on Google. [http://completeelectricalservice.com.au/] Complete Electrical Service[http://completeelectricalservice.com.au/] Complete Electrical Service is one of Canberra’s leading electrical providers. The team prides itself on using premium quality products and materials, always prioritising customer service, and handling every project from start to finish. Complete Electrical Service electricians are selected for their personality and electrical skills. They receive ongoing training in the latest techniques to ensure their work is safe, efficient and delivered to a superior standard. They offer an on-time guarantee and free testing of safety switches with every job. Additionally, if you book online you save 10 per cent on the service call fee. Here is what happy customer Paul had to say about his experience with Complete Electrical Service: “Excellent service. They were able to provide someone at short notice for a quote, and again at short notice for repairs. The electricians were friendly, easy to talk to, did great work and, unprompted, offered suggestions to reduce my power bills, which I will be taking up. They are now in my phone as the go-to electricians.” Phone: 02 6188 7021[tel:02 6188 7021] stuart@completeelectricalservice.com.au[mailto:stuart@completeelectricalservice.com.au] completeelectricalservice.com.au[http://completeelectricalservice.com.au] Unit 4, 16 Grimwade Street Mitchell ACT 2911 [https://harrisonselec.com.au/] Harrison's Electrical Canberra[https://harrisonselec.com.au/] With two fully-qualified, licensed electricians – Harrison McIntyre and Rowan Harrison – at the helm, Harrison’s Electrical Canberra can install, repair and maintain the electrics in your home or commercial space. Their range of services include general electrical work; installation of air-conditioning units; TV, data and telephone outputs; switchboard upgrades; smoke alarm installation and testing; thermal scanning; and commercial fit-outs. Harrison’s Electrical Canberra guarantees superior customer service, and will always turn up on time to provide outstanding workmanship. Your safety is the duo’s number-one concern, and they will do everything possible to keep the power in your home or commercial premises in safe working order. Phone: 02 6189 2711[tel:02 6189 2711] admin@harrisonselec.com.au[mailto:admin@harrisonselec.com.au] harrisonselec.com.au[https://harrisonselec.com.au] JM Electrical Solutions[http://www.jmelectrical.net.au] Family-owned and locally operated, JM Electrical Solutions offers 24/7 electrical services throughout the Canberra region. With customer service their priority, they guarantee premium electrical work and value for money. Offering a full range of domestic electrical installations – including switchboard upgrades, wiring safety inspections, security lighting, ceiling fans, smoke detectors and TV antennas – you are guaranteed the job will be done right. They also specialise in the supply and fitting of air-conditioning units. With no hidden fees and years of experience, JM Electrical Solutions is a professional company you can trust. Mark Rawstorn Electrical[http://markrawstornelectrical.com.au] Mark Rawstorn is an experienced Canberra electrician providing electrical installation, maintenance and repair to residential and commercial spaces. Quality, safety and professional service are Mark’s priorities, and he has been recognised for delivering excellence in the capital region by business review company Three Best Rated. Catering for all domestic electrical jobs such as lighting, wiring and switchboard upgrades, he operates Monday to Friday plus Saturday by appointment, and on Sunday for emergency call-outs. Sparks Fly Electrical[http://www.sparksflyelectrical.com.au] Sparks Fly Electrical is a leading Canberra electrical services company that prides itself on delivering quality, professional service and workmanship. With years of experience in the construction industry, the dedicated team of qualified tradies are committed to satisfying the electrical needs of every customer. Their expertise extends across residential and commercial premises, and no job is too big or too small, from power point installations to complete commercial fit-outs. Plastering services are also available and can be quoted as part of your job if you require holes repaired from the repositioning of switches, lights, fans and other appliances. Your experience with electricians in Canberra --------------------------------------------- Special thanks to our commenters who have provided insightful feedback. If you believe we have got it wrong, please let us know[https://the-riotact.com/best-of-canberra-enquiry]. Have you had any experience hiring electricians in and around Canberra? Which company did you use? Would you recommend it? Share your experience in the comments section below. Tags best of canberra[https://the-riotact.com/tag/best-of-canberra] cheap electrician canberra[https://the-riotact.com/tag/cheap-electrician-canberra] Complete Electrical Service[https://the-riotact.com/tag/complete-electrical-service] electrician[https://the-riotact.com/tag/electrician] licensed electrician[https://the-riotact.com/tag/licensed-electrician] Frequently Asked Questions -------------------------- Am I allowed to do small DIY electrical jobs at home? Absolutely not. Apart from the fact it is illegal to undertake electrical work at home unless you are a qualified electrician, it is also extremely dangerous if you don't fully understand what you are doing. If you are a licensed tradie, then go for it, but everyone else must call upon the services of a fully trained and experienced electrical tradesperson. What are the ramifications of illegal DIY electrical work? In the worst case scenario: death. Electrical wiring work can be extremely dangerous so if you are unqualified and something goes wrong, the consequences can be fatal. There is also the possibility of causing a house fire. Fines also apply for performing illegal electrical wiring work around the home. For individuals, this can be as high as $40,000. What DIY electrical work is legal for me to perform at home? Some very basic electrical jobs can be carried out at home if you are unqualified. These include installing low voltage garden lighting and pond pumps; changing a blown light bulb; installing battery operated smoke alarms; replacing LED downlights; cutting openings for air-conditioning units but not installing them; and fitting an electric wall oven but not connecting it. For everything else, use one of Canberra's best trained electricians. When should I arrange an electrical safety check? At a minimum, you should call a qualified electrician to visit your home for an electrical safety check to ensure everything is in safe working order every five years. If your property is more than 25 years old, a safety check is highly recommended, or if you simply have any concerns about how electrical items in your home have been installed. If you are purchasing a property that has been occupied, an electrical safety check is essential so you know you are buying somewhere safe. What is smart wiring and who can install it? Smart wiring is a flexible industry wiring standard that enables the combination of several types of wires into a single platform for use with smart home systems and sensors. Once installed, it allows you to access multiple telephone, internet and pay TV options, as well as audio, security, automated home lighting and integrated garden irrigation. Smart wiring systems can only be installed by an accredited smart wiring technician. electrical works. Here at Xcell Electrical Services, we have professionals who are licensed in electrical and data cabling. Our experience in the trade always leaves our customers happy with the results.
Our Services
Aside from our 24/7 electrician services, we provide other services such as lighting and installations of fibre optic cables, home entertainment systems, and security lights. We install electricity to new homes and install new electrical devices as well. We work with power points, safety switches, switchboards, and test & tagging. We also handle rewiring, renovations and repairs.
For any of your home theatre needs, we can help you! We install and design for new and existing premises and we also offer troubleshooting services.
For your lighting needs, we offer wiring, installation and designs. We can work with outdoor, pool and emergency lighting. Aside from that, we also carry out repairs, consultations, and maintenance and servicing.
More Information
We usually charge for our job based on quotes per project or per hourly rate depending on the job. We offer reasonable rates and accept either cash or direct deposit. For guarantees, we provide 6 months warranty on new installations. We are an insured company with 2 people working hard to ensure customer satisfaction.
Our standard hours of operation are from 7am to 6pm and after hours by appointment. In order for us to provide a quote, we need to know the type of house, wall materials and the complete details of the job. A site visit is required for us to provide a more accurate quote.
We offer 24/7 electrical services to our valued customers!
Our professional services are offered at a reasonable price.
Contact us for more information!</div><a class="show-more-js flat-link" id="about-us-169110" href="javascript:void(0)">Show more</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div With 15 years experience in the electrical trade, we offer a wide range of
electrical works. Here at Xcell Electrical Services, we have professionals who
are licensed in electrical and data cabling. Our experience in the trade always
leaves our customers happy with the results. Our Services Aside from our 24/7
electrician services, we provide other services such as lighting and
installations of fibre optic cables, home entertainment systems, and security
lights. We install electricity to new homes and install new electrical devices
as well. We work with power points, safety switches, switchboards, and test &
tagging. We also handle rewiring, renovations and repairs. For any of your home
theatre needs, we can help you! We install and design for new and existing
premises and we also offer troubleshooting services. For your lighting needs, we
offer wiring, installation and designs. We can work with outdoor, pool and
emergency lighting. Aside from that, we also carry out repairs, consultations,
and maintenance and servicing. More Information We usually charge for our job
based on quotes per project or per hourly rate depending on the job. We offer
reasonable rates and accept either cash or direct deposit. For guarantees, we
provide 6 months warranty on new installations. We are an insured company with 2
people working hard to ensure customer satisfaction. Our standard hours of
operation are from 7am to 6pm and after hours by appointment. In order for us to
provide a quote, we need to know the type of house, wall materials and the
complete details of the job. A site visit is required for us to provide a more
accurate quote. We offer 24/7 electrical services to our valued customers! Our
professional services are offered at a reasonable price. Contact us for more
information!

Need an Electrician in Canberra?

You’ll love our amazing service.

To find your nearest electrician

Get a free quote
Home » Areas we Service » Australian Capital Territory » Canberra

Why are we the best choice?

No waiting

Because we are an Australia-wide network, we have operatives standing by in every area of every state and territory. So when you call, we can dispatch the nearest electrician, who will arrive usually within two hours of your call. It doesn’t matter if it’s a night or weekend emergency, we’ll still be there ASAP.

Master Electricians

Our operatives are not just electricians, they’re Master Electricians. This means they’re trained to provide best practice service to the highest Australian standard, so you know the job will be done properly and safety will be their number one priority.

No answering machines

When you call some electricians, you have to negotiate an automated menu of unwanted options before you can speak to someone. Call Platinum Electricians and you will be connected directly with a real person who is already familiar with the kind of problem you may have and is ready to arrange a solution for you.

Prompt attendance

At Platinum Electricians, we take punctuality seriously. When you make an appointment with us, we guarantee that appointment will be met on time. If your electrician is late for any reason, we will reimburse you for your inconvenience with $50 cash back.

Local electricians from Canberra

Wherever you are in Canberra and whatever your electrical problem, from a faulty socket to a complete rewiring job, Platinum Electricians has the personnel and expertise to solve it fast and we back everything we do with a lifetime labour warranty.

From North Canberra to South Canberra, from Belconnen to Queanbeyan, and everywhere in between, our local electricians are ready to provide our five star service that we’re famous for all over the country.

It doesn’t matter if you’re in Gungahlin, Jerrabomberra, Majura, or Molonglo Valley – we’re local electricians and we’re close by.

Domestic or commercial, from a faulty wire to a factory refit, there’s no job too big or small for Platinum Electricians. Call us now and we’ll be anywhere in Canberra or the ACT fast.

Rest assured you’re choosing Australia’s best

As Triple Certified, multi award winners with strong and steady growth since 2001, you can have comfort that you’re partnering with a strong business – meeting and exceeding, your expectation in delivering great service.
Integrity in business is one of our core values, and you feel that straight away when you’re working with our team." - Joshua Nicholls, CEO & Founder of Platinum Electricians

Platinum is a multi-award winner

It’s always nice to be recognised for your achievements.
Checkout Media Highlights

Still more to love

Ongoing support

If we’re doing a larger maintenance or repair job for you, you can get real time updates of our work in progress, using our online customer interface. Known as Platinum Live, it also allows you to view quotes and pay invoices online.

Added value

As well as competitive rates and the option to be billed by the quote or by the hour, Platinum Electricians helps to save you money by offering cash backs and referral bonuses. We also offer Canberra residents a free electrical safety check (valued at $120), which provides a thorough inspection of your premises for potential electrical problems at no charge to you.

24/7 online access

Our customers have access to Platinum Live, our online client interface, where you can monitor work in progress, ask for quotes, pay invoices and access all of our electrical services anywhere, at any time.

Corporate services

As well as domestic electrical work, Platinum Electricians offer a range of services to business. Our nationwide team of experts are fully licensed to work on any type of electrical system. They are OHS certified and can monitor and maintain your business or industrial electrics systems, including multiple sites. Our electricians can also create a safety and maintenance plan for every situation.

We service all areas, including:

  • North Canberra
  • South Canberra

The Snowy Mountains Hydroelectric Scheme, located about two and a half hours drive from Canberra, is Australia’s largest hydro electric system.

The first power station in the ACT began operating in 1915, with Duntroon and Acton being the first areas to be supplied with electricity.

It typically takes 4 years to complete an electrician’s apprenticeship.

Renewable energy provided 17.6% of Australia’s electricity in 2016.

By 2020, wind energy will power over 80,000 Canberra homes, with the completion of several wind farm projects.

Local Electrical Facts

Make an enquiry

Speak to us now on 1800 752 846 or simply fill in the form below and a friendly member of the Platinum Electricians team will contact you shortly.

O'Brien Electrical Hume

COVID SAFE PRACTICES

O’Brien Electrical Hume remains open and our experts are here to help! We have put increased hygiene and protective measures in place to keep our customers and staff safe.

O'Brien Electrical Hume

Experts making it easy!

At O’Brien Electrical Hume, we take pride in providing high quality and dependable electrical services to you in and around Canberra, ACT and into NSW. Whether you want to engage us for residential or commercial services, our fully qualified full-time team of electricians are ready to help you.

We maintain a fleet of fully equipped vehicles run by industry-experienced electricians. We can help you with planned services or emergency electrical work. We service all areas of the ACT and surrounding NSW including Canberra, Fyshwick, Tuggeranong, Woden and Belconnen.

We cover all aspects of electrical contractors work from residential to a commercial electrician and even for the government. The team is led by brothers Andrew and Scott, who ensure that you receive outstanding customer service. All work undertaken by us complies with Australia’s health and safety requirements. When you engage us, you can rest assured you will receive quality electrical work by industry experts with friendly service.

Testimonials

"Please thank your fellow electricians for an excellent job. I just love it when tradesmen do a good job the first time around. Thanks to you also for training them so well!"

Wendy Anderson, Macarthur ACT

"Quick response to my query Detailed quote. Quick work. Cost of work was priced reasonably. Pleasant team Flexible with times. Overall, very happy with the work, time taken to complete the job, and the overall cost. Great team and friendly. A refreshing change to have great customer service from you after I've had so many bad ones with various tradies over the last few years! Well Done Laser Electrical - you stand out from the others on this and other areas as well. Thanks so much Andrew, Paul and James :)"

Virginia, Hackett ACT

"I can highly recommend O'Briens Electrical Hume! I have used Andrew and Scott for many, many years (must be getting close to two decades??) starting when they were ASN, then Laser and now O'Briens. I first engaged them for my workplace then privately for many at home jobs. Both my workplace and I continue to engage them as although they have grown in size, they are honest, reliable, very knowledgeable in all aspects of their trade and take the time to analyse every job, make recommendations, keep you informed and last but never least, clean up after themselves. Any occasional hiccup (my work building is around 60 years old with multiple renovations and switchboards - not an easy building to keep utilities running smoothly!) they have always been brilliant and are back straight away to sort (always with success!). Scott and Ryan have just yesterday installed a heat extraction unit in our top floor bedroom - great job. I have done and will continue to recommend them - these guys are great and the office staff friendly and helpful also."

Shauna, ACT

"We want to thank you and staff for the excellent work undertaken at our house. Done on time and very professional. We like to congratulate Tara and her staff of their efficiency and professionalism. Tara is excellent in managing and organising the technicians with finishing the work ahead of time. Well done guys."

Angelo, ACT

"Ashleigh and Hayden are great examples of business people who take care of their customers. Their service was prompt and they made sure that they understood what I needed and made that happen. Hayden's work was neat and tidy so much so that he impressed the neighbor to hire him for a job at their place. Thanks for the good job. I highly recommend this O'Brien team."

Michael, ACT

"We recently purchased a Tesla Model 3 and needed an electrical professionally Tesla-accredited company to instal the charger at home. The O’Brien team were excellent - prompt and professional - they did such a great job, that I also engaged them to instal a further Tesla charger at our beach shack at Malua Bay - this was a more difficult instal and involved external cabling - once again, an outstanding, thoroughly professional job by the O’Brien team. Very happy customer here."

Greg, ACT

"Thank you very much, the boys were v efficient and did a great job"

Brendan, ACT

"Please pass on my note of appreciation to Ben for coming early this morning to install the new power outlet. Quite a switched on and pleasant young man. Very professional job, too!"

Tony, ACT

"We will be back in touch, we are very, very happy with your service."

Sarah, ACT

Thank you for the prompt, excellent service – from your office staff and the tradesman who came to assist me today.

Sheena, ACT

COVID SAFE PRACTICES
--------------------

O’Brien Electrical Hume remains open and our experts are here to help! We have
put increased hygiene and protective measures in place to keep our customers and
staff safe.
O'Brien Electrical Hume
=======================
[https://www.obrien.com.au]
Experts making it easy!
-----------------------

At O’Brien Electrical Hume, we take pride in providing high quality and
dependable electrical services to you in and around Canberra, ACT and into NSW.
Whether you want to engage us for residential or commercial services, our fully
qualified full-time team of electricians are ready to help you.

We maintain a fleet of fully equipped vehicles run by industry-experienced
electricians. We can help you with planned services or emergency electrical
work. We service all areas of the ACT and surrounding NSW including Canberra,
Fyshwick, Tuggeranong, Woden and Belconnen.

We cover all aspects of electrical contractors work from residential to a
commercial electrician and even for the government. The team is led by brothers
Andrew and Scott, who ensure that you receive outstanding customer service. All
work undertaken by us complies with Australia’s health and safety requirements.
When you engage us, you can rest assured you will receive quality electrical
work by industry experts with friendly service.


Testimonials
------------
"Please thank your fellow electricians for an excellent job. I just love it when
tradesmen do a good job the first time around. Thanks to you also for training
them so well!"

Wendy Anderson, Macarthur ACT
"Quick response to my query Detailed quote. Quick work. Cost of work was priced
reasonably. Pleasant team Flexible with times. Overall, very happy with the
work, time taken to complete the job, and the overall cost. Great team and
friendly. A refreshing change to have great customer service from you after I've
had so many bad ones with various tradies over the last few years! Well Done
Laser Electrical - you stand out from the others on this and other areas as
well. Thanks so much Andrew, Paul and James :)"

Virginia, Hackett ACT
"I can highly recommend O'Briens Electrical Hume! I have used Andrew and Scott
for many, many years (must be getting close to two decades??) starting when they
were ASN, then Laser and now O'Briens. I first engaged them for my workplace
then privately for many at home jobs. Both my workplace and I continue to engage
them as although they have grown in size, they are honest, reliable, very
knowledgeable in all aspects of their trade and take the time to analyse every
job, make recommendations, keep you informed and last but never least, clean up
after themselves. Any occasional hiccup (my work building is around 60 years old
with multiple renovations and switchboards - not an easy building to keep
utilities running smoothly!) they have always been brilliant and are back
straight away to sort (always with success!). Scott and Ryan have just yesterday
installed a heat extraction unit in our top floor bedroom - great job. I have
done and will continue to recommend them - these guys are great and the office
staff friendly and helpful also."

Shauna, ACT
"We want to thank you and staff for the excellent work undertaken at our house.
Done on time and very professional. We like to congratulate Tara and her staff
of their efficiency and professionalism. Tara is excellent in managing and
organising the technicians with finishing the work ahead of time. Well done
guys."

Angelo, ACT
"Ashleigh and Hayden are great examples of business people who take care of
their customers. Their service was prompt and they made sure that they
understood what I needed and made that happen. Hayden's work was neat and tidy
so much so that he impressed the neighbor to hire him for a job at their place.
Thanks for the good job. I highly recommend this O'Brien team."

Michael, ACT
"We recently purchased a Tesla Model 3 and needed an electrical professionally
Tesla-accredited company to instal the charger at home. The O’Brien team were
excellent - prompt and professional - they did such a great job, that I also
engaged them to instal a further Tesla charger at our beach shack at Malua Bay -
this was a more difficult instal and involved external cabling - once again, an
outstanding, thoroughly professional job by the O’Brien team. Very happy
customer here."

Greg, ACT
"Thank you very much, the boys were v efficient and did a great job"

Brendan, ACT
"Please pass on my note of appreciation to Ben for coming early this morning to
install the new power outlet. Quite a switched on and pleasant young man. Very
professional job, too!"

Tony, ACT
"We will be back in touch, we are very, very happy with your service."

Sarah, ACT
Thank you for the prompt, excellent service – from your office staff and the
tradesman who came to assist me today.

Sheena, ACT
